sections.text: Terms, defined.For purposes of the Black-Tailed Prairie Dog Management Act:(1) Colony means the series of burrows and tunnels created by the black-tailed prairie dog where black-tailed prairie dogs live;(2) County board means the county board of commissioners or supervisors of a county that has adopted the act;(3) Managed colony means a colony that is confined to land owned by one person; and(4) Person means any individual, partnership, firm, limited liability company, corporation, company, society, or association, the state or any department, agency, or political subdivision thereof, or any other public or private entity.SourceLaws 2012, LB473, ยง 2.
